data.title: Great place for easy Saturday or Sunday mornings
data.text: We enjoyed a baked good or two, and a cup of java sitting on the sidewalk out front, watching the people and the workers at the nearby restaurants ready their places for their day.  The selection isn't huge, but what they have is good.  The store if full of unusual nick nacks as well as a counter for some eats...

data.title: Lunch
data.text: Ordered the Caprese sandwich. Tasty but tomatoes were sliced so thin you could barely taste them and when I said something to the waitress all she said was "well sometimes they get pretty thin". Really?

data.title: Fresh food and great beer
data.text: My wife and baby girl had an excellent meal at 1920 Tavern. The staff was excellent and they were great at helping us with our daughter. The menu is good, but the beer is over priced! This was our only negative but besides that it is a great atmosphere and place to eat.

data.title: Great place to celebrate my birthday!!!!
data.text: Some friends surprised me by taking me here for a birthday lunch.  Wow, just loved it....the food was wonderful, reasonably priced and this is a cute, quaint site to eat.  I can't wait to go back and introduce this place to my other friends!

data.title: A bit pricey
data.text: Great atmosphere, food, service but overall the prices are pretty steep. Noisy, as you might expect in the bar area up front, but we were fortunately seated in the back room where it was quieter. Wine pours are really damn skimpy with by the glass prices for an 'okay' wine in the $10-$12 range. No appetizer, 3 glasses of wine, simple but good and tasty dinners, 1 cup of coffee, no dessert, plus (20%) tip totaled $110.34. $55 each, to me, is very pricey.

data.title: Newly renovated....great food
data.text: We went to 1920 last winter and didn't enjoy being there because of the noise level in the back room.    However, the restaurant has since been renovated beautifully and it's not so loud.   We were lucky to eat outside on a beautiful night and enjoyed everything we ordered.    The sea bass was outstanding as was everything else we ordered.    Service was great and the owner, Jenna, made sure we had a wonderful time.    We will return!

data.title: Saturday lunch fare
data.text:
Walking around Roswell and decided to try this place. Unassuming and not too big, not crowded so the service was great. Don't expect 5 star dining, it's more like a sports bar. Ordered the Reuben sandwich and the Amazing burger. Both had excellent flavor and we both said would order again.
Overall it's an average place and with what we tried, it's a good place for a quick bite.

data.title: Canton Street Gem
data.text:
I'm a New Englander so when I saw the 1920 Tavern sign...thought this would be the perfect spot to have dinner with friends. Not quite like the taverns in NE, the 1920 Tavern did not disappoint. We shared the mussels with a delicious garlic infused broth that begged to be soaked up with bread; ask for lots of bread.  We had the small plates my friend and I - beef short ribs - reminiscent of Mom's Sunday pot roast; another friend had sea bass that was well put together, great taste but portion was just a bit too small. The goat cheese pound cake-something different- something delish.
The tavern is small, busy and on a Saturday night alive with people and conversations.  Our waitress was new and did a great job. Owner came over to our table to make sure all was good. So, I think I like this southern tavern, alot!

data.title: Second Stop on our Roswell Restaurant Tour!
data.text: This was the second stop as we celebrated our 20 year wedding anniversary. We were still a lttle hungry after our first stop so we walked across the street and were seated at an outside table. Dan promptly welcomed us and took our drink order. We ordered grilled oysters that were good but overly oily. We also ordered an appetizer tray of two sliced meats and one cheese. The meats were fatty and lackluster and the cheese was average. They have a nice craft beer menu but we won't be back for the food.

data.title: Just meh
data.text:
Saturday night...8:30 reservations. Ate inside, in the back (I'm not a fan of outside eating near the street). Service was fair, but the server seemed to have a chip on her shoulder. Three of us. Started with eggplant fries and the roasted oysters. Fries were the best part of the entire meal; nicely coated and crunchy outside, soft inside BUT lacking in salt. Roasted oysters were mostly breading with tiny oysters hidden underneath. They were ok. Entrees: Hamburger, Twin Filets and the Boneless short rib. Short rib-think pot roast with out ANY reasoning. It cried for salt. Served with a mushroom risotto and a nice demi glace...and some oddly shaved butternut squash- strange taste and consistency. Twin filets: OK, again needed salt. Hamburger: dry, with waaayyyyy more bun than meat. French fries were the ONLY thing salted all night. Server said it was a slow night, so attention to detail should have been on point. They also told us that they were out of more than 1/2 the beer selection and several food choices from the menu. Not good. 

Also, the gentlemen who was going to clear some of our plates wanted to do so with a cleaning bucket in his hand. At our table. While some people were still eating. Icky.

Ladies bathroom door, btw, does not lock correctly either- BEWARE. I see no need to return for meh food at a high price. There are other, better choices in the Canton Street corridor. One plus? Sandra, the woman at the hostess desk, rocked. Very attentive to my elderly dad while we were waiting to be picked up. She's a rock star!

data.title: Pricey, average, and slow
data.text:
Not rushing  back...
Waiter was extremely nice and accomodating.  But food itself was lackluster, especially given the prices.  
Caesar salad was blob of unchopped romaine with a dried piece of chicken breast.  Avoid!
Beef ribs were overcooked, but impressive in size.
Smoked chicken had nice flavor once past the black (aka burnt) skin.  
Only other complaint is while the waiter was exceptionally nice, service from the bar was DEATHLY SLOW...and it wasn't busy.  
It's hard imaging revisiting given other choices around Canton St.

data.title: Yummmmmm
data.text: A friend and I ate here before going to a show last week.  Our seat outside was comfortable.  Our waiter was attentive and efficient.  I loved the food.  Had a ravioli appetizer and a salad.

data.title: Don't go for the desserts
data.text:
My husband and I went after work during the week. We went for coffee and desserts.  We were disappointed for several reasons. First, it took too long for the desserts to be served.  Second, ice crystals were on top of the ice cream which means that no one took the time to seal the ice cream container securely. Third, the bread pudding du jour was not chocolaty like the waitress described. It was not the consistency or texture of bread pudding. Fourth, the price was too high for the value.
On a positive note, the wait staff was friendly.  Parking was only $5.

data.title: Really Enjoyed Lunch
data.text: Such a cute little place!  We ordered several things off the menu, because everything looked so good, we couldn't decide.  We really enjoyed the eggplant fries, the ruben, and the goat cheese poundcake.  Can't really recommend the tenderloin tacos...the meat was grizzly and chewy..but two of the tacos were okay...and we were still very pleased with the other three entrees we ordered (for two people ;)

data.title: Much Improved Menu. Great Service
data.text: We haven't been to 1920 in a while due to their menu. We tried them again yesterday, and were pleasantly surprised with the menu. Shelby was our server and did a fantastic job.

data.title: not sea bass
data.text:
The waitress was nice, that's about all. The sea bass I ordered was not sea bass, they agreed and said they made a mistake and it was mahi mahi, but it wasn't that either. 
They took that away and I ordered the quinoa salad with shrimp. That was really just ok, I would not go back for it.

data.title: Fabulous birthday dinner!
data.text: We went to 1920 Tavern for the first time a few days ago to celebrate my daughter's and my birthdays.  We could only get an early reservation and it was fairly empty when we arrived.  After having wonderful appetizers (an order ofcalimari and one of eggplant fries) we were far from alone. The place was packed!!! My husband had the filet and raved, my daughter had blackened tuna and raved and I had the best of all, sea bass that was perfect!  This may now be our favorite place!!

data.title: Friday Night Street side
data.text: Gorgeous summer eve with great food and service from Brittany. Startrf with crab and shrimp dip that was ok, and duck empanadas that were nice and flakey. I had blackened mahi, wife had the smoked chicken and both were very good. My son had the prosciutto wrapped Chilian seabass, that although was delicious, was not worth $32 (very small piece) and the manager knew because he had 2 orher complaints about portion size. In the end, we got a free dessert. We'll be back.

data.title: Canton street treat
data.text: This past weekend we met our friends at this Canton street treat.  Because we decided to go out last minute we decided to try 1920 Tavern as you could make reservations.  The hostesses were fantastic and the bar was hopping when we arrived.  I tried their cucumber melon cocktail which was very refreshing on that hot night.  My husband loved the house margarita.  Our server was wonderful and made great suggestions on what to try.  I never went to Inc. so the menu was all new to us.  We shared calamari, oysters and Kobe meatballs- all very tasty.  They have a great variety of small plates although the one item our friends ordered was not available.  Try the tacos!!!!! We had the tuna, steak and shrimp and they were very tasty.  You could easily eat those as an entree.  They are known for their shrimp and grits which we had no room for this visit.  The only issue that night was the air went out temporarily but was was quickly fixed.  Great cocktail choices and choices of beer on tap.  The bar was crowded on our way out and we heard other groups having as much fun as we were.  Thank you for the delicious drinks and dinner.

data.title: First Timers Lunch
data.text: My girlfriend and I shared a chopped salad. She had the Shrimp Taco Trio and I had the Mussels. Food was very satisfying and yummy. Our waitress was very attentive as she filled out water glasses a few times. Definitely a place I would return to w/family and friends.
